what is the difference between than and then than is part of the part of speech known as a comparative adjective such as hotter than better than happier than etc and requires the presence of two things or people that are being compared such as george bush is dumber than a stump is comparing two things then has several usages in the english language one usage is to suggest subsequent action as in bertha threw up then she died another usage is as a part of a two dependent clauses the first starting with the word if such as if raji buys that bmw then i will marry him hee hee i teach esl and my level of students is literacy so i never get to explain this kind of subtle differences it's fun blessings lady morgana Ford Model B Little Deuce Coupe Rob Schneider The Beach Boys Surfer Girl Beach Boys' Party! Douche Greetings from Asbury Park, N.J. Good Vibrations: Thirty Years of The Beach Boys Louie, Louie The Cure Concept album Infidels The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Kyle Broflovski All Summer Long KISS (band) Mike Love Cliff Richard Jon Secada Rod Stewart Shut Down Volume 2 She Loves You Best of The Beach Boys Beach Boys Concert Endless Harmony Soundtrack The Strokes Sounds of Summer: The Very Best of The Beach Boys Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Blues John Lennon Spike Jonze U2 (band) Three Imaginary Boys Volvo Cars Billboard Hot 100 Gary Glitter Aerosmith Smells Like Teen Spirit Blind musicians Endless Summer (album) Bohemian Rhapsody The Beatles discography Roy Orbison Spades Saint Lucy Tommy Boy B. B. King Stars and Stripes Vol. 1 Lenny Kravitz The Greatest Hits - Volume 1: 20 Good Vibrations Milton H. Erickson Joy Division (band) Keasbey Nights Buddy Holly One-hit wonder Please Please Me Hawthorne, CA (album) Good Timin': Live at Knebworth England 1980 Poker jargon Rais massacre The Meters Yankee Doodle The Biggest Douche in the Universe Lil Jon Def Leppard Rodney Anoai Surf rock A Song for Europe David Bowie The Rutles I Want to Hol